'''The Federal Service for State Registration, Cadastre and Cartography''' (Rosreestr) ({{lang-ru|Федеральная служба государственной регистрации, кадастра и картографии}}) (prior to December 30, 2008, Federal Registration Service) is a federal agency in Russia, responsible for the organization of the [[Unified State Register of Rights on Real Estate and Transactions]] ({{lang-ru|Единый государственный реестр прав на недвижимое имущество и сделок с ним}}), as well as the spatial data infrastructure of the Russian Federation. It is Russia's official [[real estate]] agency.<ref name="montenegro">{{cite news |url=https://www.bellingcat.com/news/uk-and-europe/2018/11/22/second-gru-officer-indicted-montenegro-coup-unmasked/ |date=November 22, 2018 |first=Moritz |last=Rakuszitzky |first2=Daniel |last2=Romein |first3=Roman |last3=Dobrokhotov |publisher=[[bellingcat]] |title=Second GRU Officer Indicted in Montenegro Coup Unmasked |quote=We then obtained an ownership certificate for the Moscow address from Russia’s official real estate registry, Rosreestr.}}</ref>
According to the amendments to the list of names and abbreviations of the federal bodies of executive power (the order of the [[Presidential Administration of Russia]] and the [[Government of Russia]] of July 16, 2008 № 943/788) of 2 March 2009 number P41-6596 abbreviation of the Federal Service for State Registration, Cadastre and Cartography - Rosreestr.
